description:
This is my first Getting Unstuck project for the challenge of @karenb and @paulinah: gettingunstuck.gse.harvard.edu. 

It was fun to try to come up with a pen project within a day. Therefore I needed a project idea that would not take a lot of time. I was reading a book about the micro:bit and I saw a simple robot drawing and thought it would be fun to try to make a robot using pen.

This pen project only uses lines and dots. If I had more time I would use squares too, but it's much more time consuming to make them with pen in Scratch.

I've used a random number in this kind of pen projects for the first time. I just tried it and thought it looked cool.

Do you want to see some cool examples of the use of pen in Scratch, check out these Scratchers if you like:
@hugmyster
@dapontes
@leszpio
@icampeao
@dodekagonia
@selim_tezel
@mathjp
@PullJosh

I also recommend this 100 % pen studio on Scratch: https://scratch.mit.edu/studios/3935624/

